cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DC 

This paper discusses the protection of deep neural network models from illegal reproducing and distribution, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also focuses on the performance of the DNN models, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). The use of adversarial training and crafted inputs is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the computational resources required for DNN models, which is related to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
